    "system": {
        "description": {
            "value": "<p>@UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-rules.JournalEntry.SySQiDfSWcSRUCFN.JournalEntryPage.wuMEnZz82yY02Dok#artists-tools]{Artist's Tools} are used primarily by characters to create art.</p><p>Each type of musical instrument requires a separate proficiency. When you learn an instrument, you may choose any instrument, pending your GM's approval. Alternatively, you can be a trained singer, which requires no instrument to perform music. In Elkan, musical instruments are more modern than in most 5e settings. It is reasonable if your character plays the Trombone, for example. If you have proficiency with a given musical instrument, you can add your proficiency bonus to any ability checks you make to play music with the instrument.</p>",
